The paper deals with fine-grained visual recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves deep metric learning using triplet network, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions benchmark datasets and retrieval tasks, indicating a focus on evaluation and performance analysis (cs.MM). Additionally, the use of intra-class variance suggests a potential application in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for improving feature representation and recognition accuracy.
